==English==
===Etymology===
Latin, from ''vide'' (stem of [[videre]] ‘see’) + [[licet]] ‘it is permissable’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /vɪ'dɛlɪsɛt/

===Adverb===
'''videlicet''' ''(not comparable)''
# that is to say; [[viz.]]
#:*'''1993''': My father did speak much of the day he was not speedily to forget, '''videlicet''' May Day of 1517, when there was great apprentice rioting against insolent foreigners. — Anthony Burgess, ''A Dead Man in Deptford''